Dr. Goodwin,

This is Jeff Miller from the Colorado School of Mines.  As you may 
remember, I am using Cantera to model rocket thrusters which burn a 
mixture of N2O and C2H6.  I am using reactor 1 to find the time it 
takes for 99% of the N2O to be consumed as a function of input gas 
temperature.  I am running these calculations at 100 psi, and for 
O/F ratios 4,5,6,and 10.  For O/F ratios 4, 5, and 6, this works 
great for temperatures between 1000 and 3100 K.  However, for O/F 
ratios of 10 and above, this only works for temperatures at or above 
1725 K.  For temperatures below 1725, Cantera returns the following 
error message:

Procedure: CVodeInt
Error:    CVode error encountered.

Error in ==> @ReactorNet\private\reactornetmethods at 6
  v = ctmethods(65, n, job, a);  

Error in ==> ReactorNet.advance at 22
reactornetmethods(8, reactornet_hndl(n), tout);

Error in ==> reactor1_test at 59
   advance(network, t);



What does this error mean, and what might I need to change to get 
results for this O/F ratio for temperatures lower than 1725 K?

Thank you very much,
Jeff Miller
